h3. Problem Definition
When the user creates a rule to assign the issue for someone in the first board status, the issue not get assigned.
 
h3. Steps to reproduce

# Access the next-gen project;
# Click on the board;
# In the top right click on the three dots (*...*];
# Manage rules;
# Ad rule;
# Select "Assign an issue to someone";
# In the box "For issues moving to" select the first status;
# In the box "Assign to" select the user that should be assigned.

h3. Workaround
Create a new collum as the first position and establish the rule to the second collum.

h3.Summary

The notification template formatting is inconsistent. JIRA Cloud sends notification with header at the top while the notification triggered from REST API end point (/rest/api/3/issue/<ISSUE_KEY>/notify) has header at the bottom.

h3.Replication Steps
# Trigger a notification from JIRA via normal means by performing an issue notification.
# Check out the notification from JIRA. The header of the notification will be at the top.
 !image-2020-02-27-18-27-44-668.png|thumbnail! 
# Now trigger another notification from JIRA via '/rest/api/3/issue/<ISSUE_KEY>/notify'.
{noformat}
curl -D- --request POST \
  --url 'https://kingdom-hearts.atlassian.net/rest/api/3/issue/DI-28/notify' \
  --user 'vchin@atlassian.com:<API_TOKEN>' \
  --header 'Accept: application/json' \
  --header 'Content-Type: application/json' \
  --data '{
  "htmlBody": "The <strong>latest</strong> test results for this ticket are now available.",
  "subject": "Latest test results",
  "textBody": "The latest test results for this ticket are now available.",
  "to": {
    "voters": true,
    "watchers": true,
    "groups": [
      {
        "name": "jira-software-users"
      }
    ],
    "reporter": false,
    "assignee": false,
    "users": [
      {
        "accountId": "557057:dd697c0d-6cc7-429e-b8a1-4ccab4c19347",
        "active": true
      }
    ]
  },
  "restrict": {
    "permissions": [
      {
        "key": "BROWSE"
      }
    ]
  }
}'
{noformat}
# You will notice that the header is at the bottom for this new notification.
 !screenshot-2.png|thumbnail! 

h3.Expected Result

Both notification from JIRA and JIRA REST end point should have header at the top of the notification.

h3.Current Result

JIRA notification has header at the top while JIRA REST end point notification has header at the bottom.

h3.Workaround

None so far.

h3. Issue Summary
Fields that are set as hidden in the field configuration still appear as valid options in the "Issue Detail View" within the board settings in Software projects;

h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # Create a software project;
 # Create a custom field for testing purposes. It can be of any type;
 # Make sure to not include this field in the screen associated with the issue type of your choice for that project;
 # In the field configuration scheme for that project, make sure to hide the recently created custom field;
 # Go to the board settings and select the "Issue Detail View";
 # Go to the specific field type section and click on the dropdown to show the available fields for it;

h3. Expected Results
The newly created field shouldn't appear as an option;

h3. Actual Results
The newly created custom field appears as an option.

h3. Observations
Even though we experimented with editing the context for the custom field, that didn't resolve the issue.

h3. Workaround
 Currently, there is no known workaround for this behavior. A workaround will be added here when available
